Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of data-driven analysis and model predictive control for hybrid systems, specifically bipedal walkers, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The algorithm proposed in the paper also involves machine learning techniques, such as dynamics identification and gait partitioning, which could be classified under machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the potential use of the algorithm for providing online assistance during walking, which could be relevant to the fields of control systems (cs.SY) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
